        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 11 at 4:58PM EDT until August 11 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 457 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Almont, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Capac around 500 PM EDT.
Emmett around 510 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include
Berville, Riley Center, Allenton, and Brockway.

People attending Armada Fair should seek safe shelter immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
